	            }],
            "hasLeadParagraphs": true,
            "tailParagraphs": [{
                "items": [{
                    "markupType": "Plain",
                    "text": "&#34;I wanted to [climb it] this year but this press tour came up!&#34; said Mr. Garfield, in the penthouse of the Royalton Hotel Tuesday evening. &#34;I like heights. I find heights quite fun and invigorating.&#34;",
                    "value": "",
                    "title": "",
                    "elinkItems": [],
                    "highlight": false
                }],
                "tag": "p"
            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "The actor is an experienced rock-climber, he explained.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "So why not forgo the presstour altogether? Skip elevator rides to hotel rooms in favor of scaling the heights of Africa?",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "&#34;I wish,&#34; Mr. Garfield said, laughing. &#34;I could send in body doubles and clones.&#34; Alas, he said, a reporter would be able to tell the difference.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "In addition to an aspiring Kilimanjaro conqueror, Mr. Garfield is now the &#34;ambassador of sport&#34; for Worldwide Orphans, a nonprofit run by Dr. Jane Aronson that seeks to improve the lives of orphaned children. (Spider-Man, in the famed comic books, was an orphan, after all, Dr. Aronson pointed out.)",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "The actor seems to be good at an inordinate number of things. &#34;I used to be a gymnast, a swimmer, a football player, a rugby player and a cricket player,&#34; he recalled. &#34;It doesn't matter whether you win or lose, it's how you play the game -- but that's something I didn't learn growing up. I thought if I lost then I was nothing, which is absolutely wrong, I have realized.&#34;",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "At the cocktail party for the organization, a gaggle of fans and Worldwide Orphans affiliates sipped honey-infused mixed drinks and picked at mac-n-cheese. If Mr. Garfield enjoys heights, he must have felt right at home on the top floor of the hotel, equipped with a balcony overlooking Midtown.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "Emma Stone, Mr. Garfield's &#34;Spider-Man&#34; co-star and reported girlfriend, turned heads in red heels, entering the room midway through the party. Though she declined to be interviewed, she gave Mr. Garfield a supportive kiss and gamely chatted up the Worldwide Orphans interns and employees.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "Mr. Garfield recalled his travels to Haiti and Ethiopia with Dr. Aronson, who founded World Wide Orphans in 1997.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "&#34;She taught me how to be a better human being,&#34; he said. &#34;To consider the world a community rather than individuals kicking each other in the teeth to be happy.&#34;",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "But is there something the movie-star Andrew Garfield cannot do?",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
	                "items": [{
	                    "markupType": "Plain",
	                    "text": "Yes. Although he said he &#34;constantly needs to be challenged,&#34; he does have his limits. Asked if he has plans to climb Mount Everest -- because, why not? -- he drew the line.",
	                    "value": "",
	                    "title": "",
	                    "elinkItems": [],
	                    "highlight": false
	                }],
	                "tag": "p"
	            },
	            {
